<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">362. U.S. Department of the Army. Color for Buildings. Washington, DC:GPO, 1974. Unpaginated. Index, bibl., B/W illus., color illus. </p><p class="annot">This loose-leaf technical manual is a guide for painting Armybuildings. After addressing the physical and psychological impact of color, the manual shows how to use color to advantage. An illustrated section of color schemes is coordinated with recommendations for painting everything from aircraft hangars and washrooms to homes and hospitals. Readers will find this an interesting, well-illustrated, and straightforward approach to meeting color use needs on a large scale. </p></div>
